title: Elliott's big day leads No. 1 Ohio St. past Indiana 34-27 (Yahoo Sports)
text: Posts: 54,046 Elliott's big day leads No. 1 Ohio St. past Indiana 34-27 (Yahoo Sports) Ezekiel Elliott did everything he could to keep Ohio State's winning streak going. It still took a final goal-line stand for the top-ranked Buckeyes to hold off Indiana. Elliott had an electrifying second half with touchdown runs of 55, 65 and 75 yards and finished with a career-best 274 yards as the Buckeyes narrowly won their 18th in a row - longest in the FBS.
